BP_DESCRIPTION: Blood pressure is a measure of the force that your heart uses to pump blood around your body. The systolic pressure is the pressure when your heart pushes blood out, the diastolic pressure the pressure when your heart rests between beats. Below a reference table for Blood Pressure values
sri_desc: We analyze your breathing patterns during any medical session and during your sleep. If SRI is below 30 your chances to suffer from obstructive respiratory conditions are low.
sbpi_desc: High blood pressure is the silent killer. Your Systolic and Diastolic blood pressure values are being estimated during any medical session you perform. Keep the SBPI below 30 to have lower chances to suffer from life threatening conditions such as stroke and blood clots.
sai_desc: SAI is purely based on your heart rate. It is a simple metric that tracks the bodyâ€™s response to physical activity â€“ much more than just steps. Unlike step tracking, SCI gives credit for every activity that elevates the heart rate: swimming, biking, rowing, dancing, whatever. Keep it below 30 for better and healthier life.
sci_desc: By analyzing your arterial pulse wave we are deriving insights about your cardiovascular system. The SCI index is a summary of your cardiovascular health, try to keep it below 20!
stroke_volume_desc: The stroke volume is the volume of blood ejected by each ventricle per beat
PROVIDER_TIP: Configure the providers settings for each initiative

sl_desc: The stress level is calculated based on the beat per minute
spo2_desc: SpO2 or blood oxygen level is a measure of how much oxygen your red blood cells are carrying. Normal values are between 95% and 100%, A below-normal blood oxygen level is called hypoxemia
rr_desc: The respiratory rate is the rate at which breathing occurs. The normal respiration rate for an adult at rest is 12 to 20 breaths per minute. A respiration rate under 12 or over 25 breaths per minute while resting is considered abnormal
va_desc: Vascular Age provides you a measure of the apparent age of your arteries, when compared with healthy people. If your vascular age is greater than your chronological age, you may be at more risk of developing cardiovascular disease (CVD) later in life.
cardiac_output_desc: The cardiac output is simply the amount of blood pumped by the heart per minute.
ssi_desc: By analyzing your heart rate variability we quantify your level of stress. Stress seems to worsen or increase the risk of conditions like obesity, heart disease, Alzheimer's disease, diabetes, depression, gastrointestinal problems, and asthma. Keep it below 20 to be on the safe side!
sii_desc: SII is a combination of all SaluberMD indexes and is a mirror of your general medical risk. If below 30 you are in the safe zone

ABOUT_US_SECTION2_P1:
Through geo-localization our app will find the best Physician near you. SaluberMD Physicians can diagnose, treat, or discuss your medical condition through video and provide you with an appropriate treatment plan. Many of the most common conditions treated in a doctor's office can be treated with a video visit.
Some of the conditions we treat:
ABOUT_US_SECTION2_P2: Your Personal Medical Record is a convenient place to store all of your health data, images and files. Keep track of your health with 24/7 access to all of your medical records. Whether you are at home or travelling abroad, your information is at your fingertips to share with your health professional. The easy to use personal medical record is available in 36 languages.
ABOUT_US_SECTION3_P1: Only the top board-certified Physicians provide medical care on SaluberMD. These professionals are verified, extensively screened and trained to provide the best quality care.  Each Physician has a bio where you can view their background, credentials, and experience. SaluberMD is committed to ongoing quality management of our Physicians. A rating system allows patients to rate doctors and to view a doctors overall rating.
PRICING_SECTION1_P1: SaluberMD is committed to providing convenient, quality care at affordable prices with no hidden fees or charges.
PRICING_SECTION1_P2: SaluberMD provides care wherever and whenever you need it via a video call visit with a board certified physician. Our physicians can discuss, examine, listen and diagnose your issue,  or simply address medical questions and concerns while on the video call.
PRICING_SECTION1_P3: With our exclusive Personal Medical Record you can provide your physician with access to your medical history, your images and files to help them provide the most effective treatment plan.
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_SECTION1_P1: Join the movement to provide reliable, affordable, global access to healthcare within 15 minutes or less.
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_SECTION1_P2: Saluber MD is designed to revolutionize doctor-patient relationships by creating 24/7 access to healthcare globally.
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT1_DESC: You can see up to six patients an hour (a virtual visit typically lasts about 10 minutes);
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT2: PROVIDE PATIENT CARE FROM ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD:
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT2_DESC: Increase patient relationships with the ability to treat current and new patients from anywhere in the world;
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT3_DESC: Grow your current practice and offer more options for patients;
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT4_DESC: Patients can send you documents, photos, lab results without having to leave home and you can monitor your patient's health remotely;
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT5: Identify which patients need hands on care right away and who can benefit from remote treatment without leaving home
ABOUT_US_DOCTOR_BENEFIT6_DESC: The ability to set your own hours and set your own schedule.

tipshealt6: Physical activity improves memory and thinking skills
tipshealt7: Regular physical activity can improve brain function throughout a lifespan and decrease risk of dementia.
tipshealt8: Numerous studies have been published on the close interaction and the advantage of regular physical activity and improved cognitive function.
tipshealt9: The influence is directly on the brain and indirectly through metabolic and physical actions on the body.
tipshealt11: The benefits of statins treatment, the lowering cholesterol drugs, outweigh the risks
tipshealt12: In a recent review article in Lancet, researchers concluded that the benefits of lowering LDL cholesterol with statin therapy would likely prevent major vascular events (heart attacks, strokes) and it outweighs the risks of the drugs.
tipshealt13: According to the researchers the only serious adverse events that have been shown to be caused by long-term statin therapy are myopathy (defined as muscle pain or weakness), new-onset diabetes mellitus, and, probably, haemorrhagic stroke.

valenceDescription: A variable ranging from negativity to positivity. When listening to a person talk, it is possible to understand how 'positive' or 'negative' they feel about the subject, object or event under discussion.
arousalDescription: A variable that ranges from tranquility or boredom to alertness and excitement. It corresponds to similar concepts such as level of activation and stimulation.
temperDescription: An emotional measure that covers a speaker's entire mood range. Low temper describes depressive and gloomy moods. Medium temper describes friendly, warm and embracive moods. High temper values describe confrontational, domineering and aggressive moods.
moodDescription: A key indicator of a speakerâ€™s emotional state during the analyzed voice section. The API produces a total of 11 mood groups ranging from anger, loneliness and self-control to happiness and excitement.
emotionDescription: A combination of various basic emotions, as expressed by the users voice during an analyzed voice section.
beyondverbal: Emotions drive everything we do, yet voice-driven emotions analytics remains the most important, unexplored interface today. Beyond Verbal is committed to changing that.
